      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:1:1:1:36",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        "ا سَمِعْنَا أَبَا عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) يَقُولُ لَا غِنَى أَخْصَبُ مِنَ الْعَقْلِ وَ لَا فَقْرَ أَحَطُّ مِنَ الْحُمْقِ وَ لَا اسْتِظْهَارَ فِي أَمْرٍ بِأَكْثَرَ مِنَ الْمَشُورَةِ فِيهِ "
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Muhammad, from one of his companions, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Al Nazar Bin Suweyd, from Humran and Safwan Bin Mihran Al Jammal who both said, ",
          "‘We both heard Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> saying: ‘There is no richness more enriching than the intellect, nor a poverty more abasing than the stupidity, nor anything more backing in a matter than the frequency of the consultation with regards to it’. "
        ]
      }
    }
